He wanted to prove it was “something,” he said, so he wouldn’t disappoint anyone when he eventually learned about his sexuality.
The two-time Olympic bronze medalist became an active participant in LGBT campaigns and used his participation in this year’s British Community Games in Australia to call for more countries to decriminalise homosexuality.
He said he does this because he is happy to be able to live openly, without consequences, and wants to inspire the “hope” of others.
