2004: A strong earthquake on December 26 on the western coast of Indonesia's Aceh province in North Sumatra triggered a tsunami that hit 14 countries and killed 226,000 people across the Indian Ocean coastline, more than half of them in Aceh.
2005: A series of powerful earthquakes hit the western coast of Sumatra in late March and early April.
